node.text:
Interactive story with Kirito 📚✨

 The figure steps into the light, revealing themselves as Heathcliff, the enigmatic leader of the powerful guild, the Red Roses. "You've caused quite a stir, Kirito," he says, his voice echoing in the cavern, "But your little rebellion ends now." He draws his sword, a sinister energy crackling along its edge. "I've always admired your skill, but it's time to put an end to this." He lunges, his blade faster than my eyes can follow. "You two should run," I say to Asuna, my heart pounding, "Get to safety. I'll hold him off." 

 Asuna's grip tightens on my arm, her eyes fierce, "I'm not leaving you, Kirito. We face this together, like always." I nod, determination surging in my chest. Our blades clash against Heathcliff's, sparks flying in the cavern. "You're strong, I'll give you that," he says, his smile never wavering, "But you're no match for me." He presses his advantage, his blade a whirlwind of death. I grit my teeth, pushing back against his assault, "Maybe not alone," I growl, "But with Asuna by my side, we're invincible."

 Our blades clash against Heathcliff's, the combined force of our attacks pushing him back. His smile fades, replaced by a grimace of effort. "Impressive," he grunts, "But..." He trails off, his eyes widening as a tremendous roar echoe...

node.text:
Why cozy games are good for your mental health 🌻

For me, cozy gaming has played a big role in my mental health 🥹

I remember when I used to play Animal Crossing New Leaf, and simply opening the game after a hard day, hearing the music, and talking to my villagers instantly lifted my mood. 

Animal Crossing New Horizons released at a very weird time in the world, and for a while, was my entire life. The world felt very lonely, but I found so much comfort and belonging in this game. 

This is so silly, but I still have the memory of having a bad day when I received a letter from Ava in Animal Crossing New Horizon. It said something along the lines of “I was walking along the beach when I thought of you and smiled at something you said. Never change”. And it just really touched me and was what I needed in that moment 🥹

Since then I’ve discovered more cozy games, fallen in love with their worlds and found comfort more times than I can count. 

But more so than anything - I’ve formed lasting connections and friendships with people who share a passion for cozy gaming and the comfort it brings.

Has cozy gaming (or gaming in general) had a positive impact on your mental health? Which games are the most special to you? 🌻

#cozygames #cozygaming #cozygamingcommunity #gaming

Tokyo’s Shibuya Parco shopping mall has stores featuring some of the biggest names in video games: Nintendo, Capcom, Pokemon. Now joining them is the brand new Sega store that opened on Friday.

The new retail outlet — which features merchandise from various IP, including Sonic the Hedgehog, Like a Dragon and Persona — is part of what Sega calls its “transmedia strategy” and follows the opening of a Shanghai store in May. The move is meant to increase sales of toys, clothing and other merchandise, a segment that Sega says generated ¥133 billion (about $895 million) for the company in the last fiscal year.

Read more about Sega Tokyo Store with the link in our bio.
